<!-- Cardiac Pacemaker Portfolio ------------------------------------------->
<section id="pacemaker" class="px-6 py-10 bg-gray-50 text-gray-800">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-center text-blue-700 mb-10">
    Cardiac Pacemakers: Design, Functionality & Safety Standards
  </h1>

  <!-- Evolution & Types --------------------------------------------------->
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-md rounded-xl p-6 mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">
      1. Evolution and Types of Pacemakers
    </h2>

    <p class="mb-4">
      The first implantable pacemaker appeared in 1958; modern devices feature
      lithium‑iodine batteries, micro‑processors and telemetric follow‑up.
    </p>

    <img src="pacemaker-diagrams.png"
         alt="Block diagrams of single‑ and dual‑chamber pacemakers"
         class="w-full max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-6 rounded-lg">

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- Single chamber -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-blue-700 mb-1">
          A. Single‑Chamber Pacemaker
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>One lead to right atrium <em>or</em> right ventricle</li>
          <li>Treats sinus‑node dysfunction or AF with slow VR</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- Dual chamber -->
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-lg text-blue-700 mb-1">
          B. Dual‑Chamber Pacemaker
        </h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
          <li>Leads to both right atrium and ventricle</li>
          <li>Mimics physiological AV synchrony; good for AV block</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <!-- Electrical safety --------------------------------------------------->
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-md rounded-xl p-6 mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">
      2. Electrical Safety in Pacemaker Use
    </h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
      <li>Titanium hermetic enclosure prevents leakage currents</li>
      <li>Silicone / polyurethane insulation on leads</li>
      <li>Over‑voltage suppression for defibrillator shocks</li>
      <li>EMI shielding &amp; MRI‑conditional designs</li>
    </ul>
  </article>

  <!-- Standards ----------------------------------------------------------->
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-md rounded-xl p-6 mb-10">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">
      3. Regulatory &amp; Safety Standards
    </h2>
    <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-gray-100">
          <th class="p-2 border">Standard</th>
          <th class="p-2 border">Scope</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="p-2 border">FDA PMA</td><td class="p-2 border">US Class III approval</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-2 border">ISO 14708‑1/‑2</td><td class="p-2 border">Implantable cardiac devices</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-2 border">IEC 60601‑1</td><td class="p-2 border">Electrical medical equipment</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="p-2 border">ISO 10993</td><td class="p-2 border">Biocompatibility</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </article>

  <!-- Testing ------------------------------------------------------------->
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-md rounded-xl p-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-blue-800 mb-4">
      4. Safety Testing &amp; Validation
    </h2>
    <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-2">
      <li>Bench: battery longevity, output load, impedance</li>
      <li>Accelerated aging &amp; hermeticity checks</li>
      <li>Pre‑clinical animal studies for tissue response</li>
      <li>Human clinical trials (Phase I–III) for efficacy &amp; safety</li>
      <li>Software verification, redundancy &amp; watchdog timers</li>
    </ul>
  </article>
</section>
